<h3> What just went on? </h3>
<div class="docs-body">
	<p> The submit button triggered the following web request </p>
	<div class="code">
	<%= textilize("<pre>#{url}
	</pre>").html_safe %>
	</div>
	<p> The output response contains the following fields that can be parsed in the way we want. </p>
	<div class="code">
	<%= textilize(
		"<pre>
		product_id: integer;
		name: text;
		image_*: text (urls);
		image_trimmed: text (url for full size image);
		average_rating: integer;
		total_rating_count: integer;
		product_url: text (url on milo site);
		merchants: list of integers;
		min_price,max_price: integer (in pennies);
		on_sale: true or false;
		category_tree: dot separated category tree;
		upc,isbn,asin,ean: text;
		</pre>"
	).html_safe%>	
	</div>
	<p> Other product attributes are available that provide more product details. </p>
	<div class="code">
	<%= textilize(
		"<pre>
		attributes {
		color: { text, text};
		size: {text, text}; }
		</pre>"
	).html_safe%>	
	</div>
	<p> If you look at the results, top ten are shown as a demonstration.  </p>
